cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes an end-to-end architecture for abnormal chest X-ray identification using deep neural networks and generative adversarial one-class learning. This involves image classification and reconstruction, which are common tasks in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of generative adversarial learning also suggests a potential overlap with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
